Pan American World Airways returns to the Hawaiian Islands with service from New
York and Los Angeles beginning on November 20, 1987. To commemorate the event,
this cover has been produced by Cary Bean of Eugene, Oregon, and Fred Nott, a
former Pan American employee.
The airplane shown on the cover is a Pan Am Boeing 747. As an added feature, the
1985-44¢ Trans-Pacific International Air Mail stamp was used for postage.
The covers were flown to Honolulu on Pan American flight number 81 on November
20, 1987 by Fred Nott.
The covers were serviced at the Honolulu Air Mail Facility.
The producers thank the Public Relations Department, Pan American World Airways,
Inc., New York, N.Y., Mr. James Arey, Systems Director, for their assistance.
